SUMMARY:Veneration of the Cross
DESCRIPTION:Veneration of the Cross\nFriday\, April 3 | 7:30 PM (streamed)\nThe tradition of venerating the cross began in the 4th century with a Spanish nun who\, on Holy Friday\, would display parts of the holy wood of the cross on which Christ died\, for veneration by pilgrims. This custom made its way into several liturgies as part of the Triduum\, the three-day period from Maundy Thursday through Easter Eve. \nWe venerate the cross not because Christ died on it\, but because by the cross\, salvation has entered the whole world. Click here to view the service from our streaming services page.
URL:https://www.saintjameslancaster.org/event/veneration-of-the-cross-2/
LOCATION:Saint James Episcopal Church\, 103 North Duke Street\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17602\, United States
CATEGORIES:Holy Week
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.saintjameslancaster.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/VenerationoftheCross.jpg
GEO:40.040058;-76.30344
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Saint James Episcopal Church 103 North Duke Street Lancaster PA 17602 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=103 North Duke Street:geo:-76.30344,40.040058
END:VEVENT
